.TH "ABSTRACTRANGE.COLLAPSED" "3JS" "January 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
AbstractRange.collapsed \- AbstractRange: collapsed property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]collapsed\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]AbstractRange\f[R] interface returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if the
range\(cqs start position and end position are the same.
.PP
A collapsed range is empty (containing no content), and specifies a
single point in a DOM tree.
To collapse a range, see the \f[CR]Range.collapse()\f[R] method.
.SH VALUE
A boolean value which is \f[CR]true\f[R] if the range is
\f[I]collapsed\f[R].
A collapsed range is one in which the start and end positions are the
same, resulting in a zero\-character\-long range.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] range = document.createRange();
range.setStart(startNode, startOffset);
range.setEnd(endNode, endOffset);

\f[B]const\f[R] isCollapsed = range.collapsed;
.EE
